--- title: ResNet Backbone keywords: fastai sidebar: home_sidebar summary: "Functions to set up a ImageNet pre-trained ResNet backbone to fine-tune on a generic dataset." ---

conv3x3[source]

conv3x3(in_planes, out_planes, stride=1)

Return a 3x3 convolution taking in in_planes filters and outputting out_planes filters with padding and stride stride.

conv1x1[source]

conv1x1(in_planes, out_planes, stride=1)

Return a 1x1 convolution taking in in_planes filters and outputting out_planes filters with padding and stride stride.

class BasicBlock[source]

BasicBlock(inplanes, planes, stride=1, downsample=None) :: Module

The basic building block for ResNets, encompassing the residual connection.

Args: inplanes: number of input filters planes: number of output filters stride: stride of the first 3x3 conv downsample: whether to downsample the input of the block

class Bottleneck[source]

Bottleneck(inplanes, planes, stride=1, downsample=None) :: Module

The bottleneck block for ResNets, encompassing the residual connection.

Args: inplanes: number of input filters planes: number of output filters stride: stride of the first 3x3 conv downsample: whether to downsample the input of the block

class ResNet[source]

ResNet(block, layers, num_classes=1000) :: Module

Constructs a ResNet using a block specification and number of layers.

Args: block: the building block for the ResNet (i.e. BasicBlock or Bottleneck) layers: a list of 4 integers, specifying the number of layers in each block num_classes: the number of output classes (defaults to 1000)

resnet18[source]

resnet18(pretrained=False, **kwargs)

Constructs a ResNet-18 model. Args: pretrained (bool): If True, returns a model pre-trained on ImageNet

These are the main functions by which you should be constructing ResNets, as they correspond to the structures used when training on ImageNet. For example:

model = resnet50(pretrained=True, num_classes=4);

model

Note that the last layer of the model being constructed is a linear layer constructed from scratch, i.e. it has no pre-trained weights associated with it. This is to allow for fine-tuning just the last layer on the downstream classification task of choice.
